# Adenylate-uridylate-rich elements (AU-rich elements; AREs) are specific nucleotide sequences located in the 3' untranslated region (UTR) of messenger RNAs (mRNAs) that act as key regulators of mRNA stability and translation. 
# They typically contain the motif AUUUA and function to trigger rapid decay of mRNAs that encode transient proteins like cytokines and proto-oncogenes, controlling essential cellular processes.
